    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к *%ibāraka%i-, от не сохранившегося самостоятельно глагола
        %ibār-%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8bar"/>] ‘ездить верхом’ (как <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_maræg"/> ‘убийца’ от %imar%i- [см. <ref type="xr"/>], <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_daræg"/> ‘кормилец’ от %idar%i- [см. <ref type="xr"/>], <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_zaræg"/> ‘певец’ от zar- [см. <ref type="xr"/>]). Ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>bar-</w><gloss><q>ездить верхом</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
            ><lang/><w>asa-bāra-</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned
            xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>asa</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>). Из
        многочисленных других иранских соответствий можно отметить: <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                ><lang/><w>vār-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                    ><w>vōra</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><biblScope>Тр.
                Тадж. базы АН СССР 1940 IX 103</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*βārāk</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βārē(β'r'k,
                β'ryh)</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><w>βārākčīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w>*βārēčīk</w><gloss><q>верховая лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>, (см.:
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>bārgya-</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w>bāraa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">из <mentioned
                    xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>*bāraka)</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="en">from <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>*bāraka)</w></mentioned></note><gloss><q>верховое
            животное</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w>aśśa-bāraa</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>bārak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>bāragī</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="srh"><lang/><w>wərok</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="srh"
                    ><w>worak</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>worj</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>. — К
        осетинскому примыкает <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/><w>berij</w></mentioned> (←
        %ibaræg%i), <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
            ><lang/><w>bärij</w><gloss><q>молодец</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>удалец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>джигит</q></gloss></mentioned>, (как <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                ><lang/><w>merij</w><gloss><q>убийца</q></gloss></mentioned> из <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_maræg"/>). — Исчезновению глагола <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8bar"/> в
        значении ‘ездить верхом’ способствовало, вероятно, то, что в осетинском есть еще два глагола
        такого же звучания: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_baryn"/> ‘взвешивать’ и <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_baryn"/> ‘прощать’. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bajrag"/>
        ‘жеребенок’, а также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bal"/> и <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_balc"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                50</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to *%ibāraka%i-, from the verb %ibār%i- [see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_8bar"/>] ‘ride’ which is not in usage anymore (like <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_maræg"/> ‘killer’ from %imar%i- [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_maryn"
        />], <ref type="xr" target="#entry_daræg"/> ‘feeder’ from %idar%i- [see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_daryn"/>], <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zaræg"/> ‘singer’ from %izar%i-
        [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zaryn"/>]). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>bar-</w><gloss><q>ride</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>asa-bāra-</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned
            xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>asa</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>). There should
        be mentioned the following Iranian correspondences among others: <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                ><lang/><w>vār-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                    ><w>vōra</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><biblScope>Trudy
                Tadžikskoj bazy AN SSSR 1940 IX 103</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*βārāk</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βārē(β'r'k,
                β'ryh)</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><w>βārākčīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w>*βārēčīk</w><gloss><q>riding horse</q></gloss></mentioned>, (see: <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>bārgya-</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w>bāraa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">из <mentioned
                    xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>*bāraka)</w></mentioned></note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="en">from <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>*bāraka)</w></mentioned></note><gloss><q>riding
            animal</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w>aśśa-bāraa</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>bārak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>bāragī</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="srh"><lang/><w>wərok</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="srh"
                    ><w>worak</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>worj</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The
        following words are close to Ossetic: <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
            ><lang/><w>berij</w></mentioned> (← %ibaræg%i), <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                ><lang/><w>bärij</w><gloss><q>good person</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="inh"><w/><gloss><q>daredevil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="inh"><w/><gloss><q>jigit</q></gloss></mentioned>, (like <mentioned
            xml:lang="inh"><lang/><w>merij</w><gloss><q>killer</q></gloss></mentioned> from <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_maræg"/>). — The loss of the verb <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_8bar"/> in the meaning 'ride' was made real because of two Ossetic verbs
        of the same pronounciation: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_baryn"/> ‘weigh’ and <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_baryn"/> ‘forgive’. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bajrag"/>
        ‘foal’, and also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bal"/> and <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_balc"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                50</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
